Only one alternate case scenario for toxic chemicals on Chambers works extends off-site and could potentially impact the local community depending on the wind direction at the time of release.  The scenario is a pipe leak of nitric acid (conc. 80% or greater).  The other alternative scenarios may reach beyond the site boundary but the endpoint distances do not reach populated areas.  Emergency procedures and mitigation equipment are in place to prevent and respond, as needed, to these scenarios.



In addition to release prevention measures, the site maintains a highly trained and equipped emergency response department around the clock.  They are able to respond to any chemical release and mitigate the impact.  To address a situation like the alternate scenarios described above, Chambers Works has an emergency response and fire truck equipped with chemical resistant foam.  This foam can be sprayed over the spill and smother the fume release.



